(100200500124004, 'Filgrastim', 'Filgrastim \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n More information Filgrastim  (NCI Drug Dictionary) Filgrastim  (MedlinePlus) \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n What are the other names for this drug? What types of cancers is this drug used to treat? How does this drug work? How is this drug given? What side effects can be caused by drug? What should I tell my doctor before taking this drug? What are the other names for this drug? Generic name:  Filgrastim (fil-GRA-stim) Trade name:  Neupogen&#174; Other:  Granulocyte Colony Stimulating Factor (G-CSF) What types of cancers is this drug used to treat? Filgrastim is not used to treat cancer. It is used to decreases the risk of infection. How does this drug work? This drug is speeds up the recovery of the white blood cells (WBC) after chemotherapy. How is this drug given? Filgrastim may be given intravenously (IV) or injection under the skin (subcutaneous, SubQ). It is given several days after chemotherapy. Blood tests are done to check your body\'s response to this drug. What side effects can be caused by this drug? You may have none, some, or all side effects listed. Or, you may have side effects that are not listed here. There are many ways to help lessen or prevent side effects. Side effects almost always go away after treatment. Some side effects are more serious than others. Your doctor or nurse will tell you what side effects they need to know about right away. COMMON SIDE EFFECTS Pain  (bone; typically in the back or legs)  LESS COMMON SIDE EFFECTS Fever  Headache, generalized aches and pains  SERIOUS SIDE EFFECTS  Extreme  fatigue Shortness of breath  Fast or irregular heartbeats  Rash  Signs of infection ( fever  of 101.0 degrees Farenheit or higher, chills)  What should I tell my doctor before taking this drug? Before taking this drug, make sure to tell your doctor if you:  Have any allergies.   Are taking any other drugs, such as over-the-counter drugs, vitamins, or herbal products.   Are thinking about having a child or have a partner that could become pregnant. This drug may be unsafe to the pregnancy. Ask your doctor about when it might be safe to have a child. Women choosing to breastfeed should talk to their doctor before nursing.  Return to top \r\n\r\n '),
