(100200500137004, 'Lomustine', 'Lomustine \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n More information Lomustine  (NCI Drug Dictionary) Lomustine  (MedlinePlus) \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n What are the other names for this drug? What types of cancers is this drug used to treat? How does this drug work? How is this drug given? What side effects can be caused by drug? What should I tell my doctor before taking this drug? What are the other names for this drug? Generic name: Lomustine (loh-MUS-teen) Trade name: CeeNU&#174; Other names: CCNU  What types of cancers is this drug used to treat? Lomustine may be used to treat brain tumors, Hodgkin\'s disease, non-Hodgkin\'s lymphoma, melanoma, lung cancer, and colon cancer.  How does this drug work? This drug is a chemotherapy (KEEM-o-TH-AIR-a-pee) drug.  It "wipes out" or kills rapidly dividing cells, such as cancer cells.  There are many kinds of chemotherapy drugs.  Doctors divide these drugs into different groups based on how they affect cells in the body.  Lomustine is in the "alkylating agent" (L-ka-Late-ing Agent) group.  Alkylating agents damage the DNA of a cell and cancer cells are more sensitive to this type of DNA damage.  How is this drug given? Lomustine is taken by mouth as a capsule.  It comes in both a blue or green capsule.  Taking this capsule on an empty stomach may help to reduce side effects.  What side effects can be caused by drug? You may have none, some, or all side effects listed.  Or, you may have side effects that are not listed here.  There are many ways to help lessen or prevent side effects.  After treatment, side effects almost always go away. Some side effects are more serious than others.  Your doctor or nurse will tell you what side effects they need to know about right away. COMMON SIDE EFFECTS  Low blood cell counts (increased risk of bleeding, infection resulting from  neutropenia , or  anemia  Feeling sick ( nausea  Vomiting   Loss of appetite  Shortness of breath Weakness Fatigue Fever , chills, tremor,  anxiety LESS COMMON SIDE EFFECTS Mouth sores  Loss of fertility (This drug may affect ability get pregnant or father a child.)  SERIOUS SIDE EFFECTS  Vomiting (more than 4 times in 24 hours)  Cough shortness of breath Mouth sores  Dizziness,  weakness , headache, or confusion   Extreme  fatigue  or sleepiness   Strange bleeding or bruising   Signs of infection ( fever  of 101.0 degrees Farenheit or higher, chills)  What should I tell my doctor before taking this drug? Before taking this drug, make sure to tell your doctor if you:  Have any allergies.   Are taking any other drugs, such as over-the-counter drugs, vitamins, or herbal products.   Are thinking about having a child or have a partner that could become pregnant. This drug may be unsafe to the pregnancy. Ask your doctor about when it might be safe to have a child. Women choosing to breastfeed should talk to their doctor before nursing.  Return to top \r\n\r\n '),
