(100200500140004, 'Mitomycin', 'Mitomycin \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n More information Mitomycin  (NCI Drug Dictionary) Mitomycin  (MedlinePlus) \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n What are the other names for this drug? What types of cancers is this drug used to treat? How does this drug work? How is this drug given? What side effects can be caused by drug? What should I tell my doctor before taking this drug? What are the other names for this drug? Generic name: Mitomycin (mye-toe-MYE-sin) Trade names: Mitozytrex&#174;, Mutamycin&#174; Other names: Mitomycin-C, MTC, Mutamycin  What types of cancers is this drug used to treat? Mitomycin may be used to treat adenocarcinoma of the stomach or pancreas.  It can also be prescribed for treatment of anal bladder, breast, cervical, colorectal, head and neck, and non-small cell lung cancer. How does this drug work? This drug is a chemotherapy (KEEM-o-TH-AIR-a-pee) drug.  It "wipes out" or kills rapidly dividing cells, such as cancer cells.  There are many kinds of chemotherapy drugs.  Doctors divide these drugs into different groups based on how they affect cells in the body.  Mitomycin is in the "anti-tumor antibiotic" group.  How is this drug given? Mitomycin is given intravenously (IV).  This drug could be very irritating to the skin if any leaked out from the vein.  If you feel any burning or notice a change in sensation along your arm while the drug is infusing, immediately notify a nurse. What side effects can be caused by drug? You may have none, some, or all side effects listed.  Or, you may have side effects that are not listed here.  There are many ways to help lessen or prevent side effects.  After treatment, side effects almost always go away. Some side effects are more serious than others.  Your doctor or nurse will tell you what side effects they need to know about right away. COMMON SIDE EFFECTS  Low blood cell counts (increased risk of bleeding, infection resulting from  neutropenia , or  anemia Weakness Fatigue LESS COMMON SI