(100200500141004, 'Oxaliplatin', 'Oxaliplatin \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n More information Oxaliplatin  (NCI Drug Dictionary) Oxaliplatin  (MedlinePlus) \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n What are the other names for this drug? What types of cancers is this drug used to treat? How does this drug work? How is this drug given? What side effects can be caused by drug? What should I tell my doctor before taking this drug? What are the other names for this drug? Generic name: Oxaliplatin (ox-a-ee-PLA-tin) Trade name:  Eloxatin&#174; Other names: None  What types of cancers is this drug used to treat? Oxaliplatin may be used to treat colon or rectal cancer. How does this drug work? This drug is a chemotherapy (KEEM-o-TH-AIR-a-pee) drug. It "wipes out" or kills rapidly dividing cells, such as cancer cells. There are many kinds of chemotherapy drugs. Doctors divide these drugs into different groups based on how they affect cells in the body. Oxaliplatin is in the "alkylating agent" (L-ka-Late-ing Agent) group. Alkylating agents damage the DNA of a cell and cancer cells are more sensitive to this type of DNA damage.  How is this drug given? Oxaliplatin is given intravenously (IV) as a rapid infusion.  What side effects can be caused by drug? You may have none, some, or all side effects listed. Or, you may have side effects that are not listed here. There are many ways to help lessen or prevent side effects. After treatment, side effects almost always go away. Some side effects are more serious than others. Your doctor or nurse will tell you what side effects they need to know about right away. COMMON SIDE EFFECTS  Low blood cell counts (increased risk of bleeding, infection resulting from  neutropenia , or  anemia  Feeling sick ( nausea  Vomiting  Diarrhea  Numbness or tingling in hands or feet (It is important to report your symptoms to your doctor. These side effects may be controlled by slightly lowering the dose of the drug.)  LESS COMMON SIDE EFFECTS  Difficulty breathing or swallowing  